alert.note: Alert for Clallam (Washington) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued December 05 at 5:16AM PST until December 05 at 6:00PM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...Observed flooding changed to Minor severity and increased in duration for the following rivers in Washington... Bogachiel River Near La Push affecting Clallam County. .Heavy rain over the area has come to an end this morning. The Bogachiel is cresting and will begin to recede later this morning. ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL THIS EVENING... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring. * WHERE...Bogachiel River near La Push. * WHEN...Until this evening. * IMPACTS...At 37.0 feet, the Bogachiel River will cause flooding of State Highway 110 near the Bogachiel bridge...closing the road. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 4:30 AM PST Tuesday the stage was 38.6 feet. - Flood stage is 37.0 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 4:30 AM PST Tuesday was 38.6 feet. - Forecast...The river is cresting around 38.6 feet. The river will begin to recede by midday and fall back below flood stage late this afternoon or evening. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Be especially cautious at night when it is harder to recognize the dangers of flooding. Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued by this afternoon at 130 PM PST.
